description.narrative: (Kazakhstan): The overall objective of the Kazakhstan Judicial Program (KJP) is to strengthen the independence of Kazakhstan's judiciary, building on the Supreme Court's aspirations to improve public trust in the courts and demonstrating greater alignment with internationally recognized standards of accountability and performance. FY 2018 funding will be used to provide targeted technical assistance and training to judicial institutions, including the Union of Judges, and Academy of Justice. In line with the Mission's efforts to strengthen GOK institutions (ICS Objective 3.1), KJP will train judges in decision-writing techniques, support the implementation of new legislation, and promote alternative dispute resolution methods. KJP also helps improve the Government of Kazakhstan's capacity to mediate business disputes and safeguard intellectual property rights. These interventions will positively influence investment climate in Kazakhstan, as well as will help to protect rights and interests of U.S. companies, thereby helping promote American prosperity (NSS Pillar II). In addition, KJP builds the capacity of the Kazakhstani judiciary to prevent violent extremism by improving procedures for categorizing and trying extremism cases (NSS Pillar I). As effective court system is often regarded as a cornerstone of lasting development, KJP's work to strengthen Kazakhstan's judiciary is a promising way to enhance the country's institutional capacity for self-reliance.
